Core Data Types (Bits & Meaning)


1- Integer types (whole numbers)

Data type	Bits	Bytes	Range (approx)	Use case

int8	8 bits	1 byte	-128 to 127	very small numbers, memory-critical

int16	16 bits	2 bytes	-32,768 to 32,767	small integers

int32	32 bits	4 bytes	-2.1B to 2.1B	standard integers

int64	64 bits	8 bytes	-9.22-10¹⁸ to 9.22-10¹⁸	default on modern systems

👉 Each element uses these bits independently

2- Floating-point types (decimal numbers)

Data type	Bits	Bytes	Precision	Use case

float16	16 bits	2 bytes	~3 decimal digits	GPUs, memory saving

float32	32 bits	4 bytes	~7 decimal digits	ML, graphics

float64	64 bits	8 bytes	~15-16 digits	default NumPy float


👉 float64 is what you-ve been seeing most often.

3- Boolean type

Data type	Bits	Meaning

bool	8 bits (1 byte)	True or False


Even though only 1 bit is needed, CPUs store it as 1 byte for speed.

4- Character / String types (NumPy)


Data type	 Meaning Bits
<U1	        1 Unicode character	 32 bits
<U10	    up to 10 characters	 320 bits
<U21	    up to 21 characters	 672 bits

👉 Strings are fixed-size in NumPy, unlike Python strings.
